GeneralDesc: SEL-2533 T2 Low Pressure alarm indicated in Vantage as of 0111 on 04/05/18 SEL-2533 T1 Low Pressure alarm indicated in Vantage as of 0514 on 04/05/18.
CompletionDesc: 5 April: I responded to a C4 alert that the GSU was indicating a Low Pressure Alarm. When I arrived at the transformer, the SEL 2414 was enunciating a Low Nitrogen Pressure alarm. I acknowledged the alarm and then cleared it. It did clear, which means the condition was no longer occurring. I went to the nitrogen cabinet and observed the high/low contact set points. They are adjustable. The high/low were not in their prescribed setting, which is -2 and +7. I adjusted the contacts and we will monitor to see if this situation occurs again..

GeneralDesc: WO-00007208 ; IS 46 ; Central Inverter - Production Outage ;. Inverter E-A7-2 offline. Modules damaged causing ground fault. CB to be isolated.---Created By; Julien Glover on: 10/26/2017. 001 - Ground fault
CompletionDesc: 26 Oct: We were alerted to an inverter outage at E-A7-2 at 1045. Upon investigation, we discovered that a skid-steer operator from HBC (working on the site roads per Punchlist) hit two modules. This caused a Ground Fault in the array and tripped the inverter offline. Pictures Attached. Work Performed: We alerted Entropy (as they are the responsible contractor) and HBC. The supervisors for both came to the location. In an effort to get the inverter back online asap, CCR took lead. CCR Opened and LOTO'd the applicable CB. We then cleared and reset the inverter. It came back online with no issues. It was producing again by 1130. At that time, Entropy was cleared to replace the broken modules. CCR ensured the Source-Circuits were unplugged before work began. Entropy workers had the modules replaced within 30 minutes. CCR then inspected the work, connected the Source Circuit wiring to the String Wiring and took voltage measurements to ensure proper Voc. The fuses in the CB were tested and tested OK. All string touch-safe fuse holders were closed in with the exception of the string that was just addressed with the repair. The CB was then CLOSED in and voltage/current measurements were taken to ensure there were no issues. Lastly, the repaired string was closed in and held with no issues. The area was cleaned and cleared with no issues and all repairs were successful.. TechDispatched: No

DC wiring is Red and White to positive, and Black to negative. 2. Email security@gridsme.com and rush.ferrell@ccrenew.com. Instruct them of what farm you are at and what modem IMEI you have with you. GeneralDesc: Replacement of cell modem to current spec Sierra Wireless. 1. Arrive on site; open DAS cabinet; wire in the new cell modem with the shipped antenna while the old modem and antenna are still in place and powered on. a. DC wiring is Red and White to positive, and Black to negative. 2. Email security@gridsme.com and rush.ferrell@ccrenew.com. Instruct them of what farm you are at and what modem IMEI you have with you. The IMEI will be listed on the box as well as the sticker on the bottom side of the modem. 3. GridSME will begin matching up all of the modem settings. And you are free to perform any other tasks you are on site for. 4. Once the migration is complete, GridSME will notify you via email. 5. Uninstall the old modem, leaving the antenna, and permanently install the new modem. 6. Leave site with the old cell modem and the shipped antenna..

GeneralDesc: POA 2 Reading High. There is a 3% variance between POA 1 and 2. We need to check the angle of the POAs and the check that the programmed calibration coefficient matches the correct POA. There might be some shading on POA in the morning also.. 0000 - Unknown
CompletionDesc: Checked installation, tilt, and azimuth. No measurable difference between the two POAs was discovered. Both POAs are in the same location at the end of the array near the inverter pad. One is mounted midway up the top-row adjacent module, and the other is midway up the bottom-row adjacent module. This will cause variations in irradiance between the two since the bottom one will not be in full view of the sun like the one above it. Definitely bottom POA shading in the AM, and the afternoon from the inverter pad since it?s mounted so low. See attached link for photos https://ccrenew.box.com/s/4pquclgggy58arbka8ngeyrzlr5ir3u2. TechDispatched: Yes

GeneralDesc: Sunfish Down Strings 2019 Hi-Fly. 19 Down Strings found during UAS high fly. ~5 fixed on CB 2.16 on day of the scan Pure Power is to be onsite finishing module installation under WO-227317. While onsite they will repair the remaining down strings. Drone report/images shared with PP.. 0000 - Unknown
CompletionDesc: Here were our findings at Sunfish today, 10/23/2019. Come to find out, these strings were the ones that Ryan, with Pure Power, said they didn?t fix: - 1.3.8 top - 1.10.3 bot - 3.13.3 bot However, here were the only two strings that we found offline in the field: - 2.13.16 (wasn?t on the list of strings that they didn?t fix)- Down due to module lead severed at j-box. We swapped module and string is now producing. - 3.13.3- Down due to melted mod to mod connector. Connectors were replaced and string is now producing. There are still a number of damaged modules onsite, including some shattered and some faulty Trina 305s. Also, string morning shading in both arrays 1 and 3, especially prior to 11am, causing some underperformance. However, all in all, the site probably looks the best it has in a couple of years? I?ll update WO 1046898 with these findings, and the hi-fly scan videos/images will be up in Box in the UAS folder before long.

Contractor performed inspections and testing to transformer 1 and MV cables from transformer to riser pole to determine health of transformer and cables. GeneralDesc: WO-00005725 ; IS 46 ; Central Inverter - Communications Outage ;. Inverter E-B5-1 has intermittent communications.---Created By; Joseph Sheffield on: 08/17/2017. 020 - Data/Communication System Outage
CompletionDesc: 14 August: E-B5-1 is the new inverter that was commissioned last week. It has had intermittent comms since Monday (14 Aug). It would go down and then come back up. I called Martin (Kaco tech) on Monday and he said to monitor it. The issue continued until today. 17 August: Today (17 Aug) the comms never came online this morning. We went back to the field and tried to reset the inverter at the HMI and this was not successful. I called Martin again and he walked us through the process of reloading the HMI software using an SD card from the neighboring inverter. We followed his steps exactly but this did not bring the inverter back online. Martin is scheduled to come out tomorrow and he will be bringing an new HMI. 23 August: Kaco has been working on site since Monday (21 August) performing the PRC-024 inverter software updates. I had them evaluate E-B5-1 again. As we monitored E-B5 throughout the day, we noticed that when it was communicating E-B7 was not, and when E-B7 was communicating E-B5 was not. Once we explained that to the Kaco technician, they went back to E-B5 and reprogrammed the HMI. The issue was that E-B5 and E-B7 had the same addresses. That has been fixed now and both E-B7 and E-B5 are communicating normally now.. TechDispatched: No

The hot spot is on the feeder cable as it transitions to the jumper just above the cold shrink, pointing to a loose connection, or crimp that?s not making good contact. The cable here is called out to be 25kV. Attached is the MV SLD, and thermal/HD images of the pole. The SLD actually calls out for there to be fused cutouts here, but there are none.. 010 - Over temperature

The MV contractor also checked and replaced eastern most Phase termination due to confusion on which phase was hot. We should attempt to clarify specific phase letter in the future to avoid confusion.

GeneralDesc: WO-00009593 ; Bladen ; Other - Other ;. Acknowledged alarms in the Bladen SCADA, but the alarms did not clear. The alarms are as follows, Comm error for SCADASVR, Met station 2 comm fail, SEL 2533 loss of motor ac on C2, loss of AC power on D2, and SEL 351S breaker trouble alarm---Created By; Sean M. McCormick on: 03/08/2018. 020 - Data/Communication System Outage
CompletionDesc: 14 March 2018: I responded to the report of multiple alarms at Bladen today. After checking in with C4, I entered the Control Room and did a general check of the room, batteries, SCADA rack, 351's and electrical panels. I checked that all breakers were closed and not tripped. Then, I donned my PPE and entered the yard. I checked the five Feeder Breakers and all 351's were Station Normal. I then went to the transformer and evaluated the SEL's there. They were Station Normal. Lastly, I went to the SF6 (high side breaker) and it had multiple alarms. I acknowledged them and then cleared them. Since they cleared, that issue was not longer present. Then, I went to the sump pump well. That alarm would not clear so I manually turned it off, drained the water from the well and cleaned the oil probe. Afterwards, I reset the sump alarm and it did not alarm anymore. I called C4, asked them to check all alarms and I was told that all the alarms had cleared.. TechDispatched: No

GeneralDesc: WO-00005976 ; IS 46 ; Central Inverter - Production Outage ;. Inverter E-A7-1 has faulted offline.---Created By; Joseph Sheffield on: 09/05/2017. 019 - Unplanned outage/derate
CompletionDesc: Sept 5: Technician went to inverter to investigate it being online but showing 0 kW production. The inverter was found to be in fault and was not producing. The following steps were utilized to successfully clear the fault: 1) The DC disconnects were placed in the OPEN position. 2) The inverter was keyed to the OFF position. 3) Circuit Breaker 21 was placed in the OPEN position. 4) Technicians opened the HMI cabinet and visually inspected the various breakers inside the cabinet. Two were found to be in the OPEN position. Technician cycled them and placed them in the CLOSED position. 4) GFI breaker was visually checked and found to be in the CLOSED position. 5) The inverter was closed back up and restarted according to the manufacturer's instructions. 6) The inverter came back online and began production after the mandatory AC sync period.. TechDispatched: No
